With Generalization: Reusable Method
1 public void createArrays() {
2 int[] array1 = initArray(3);
3 int[] array2 = initArray(6);
4 }
5
6 public int[] initArray(int n) {
7 int[] arr = new int[n];
8 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
9 arr[i] = i;
10 return arr;
11 }
This version avoids duplication by generalizing the repeated logic into a
helper method.
